@*
    [TR] Bu dosya ne işe yarar: Genel karşılama sayfası — proje tanıtımı, özellik kartları, gelecek çalışmalar notu.
    [TR] Neden gerekli: Savunmada sistemin kapsamını tek ekranda özetler; varsayılan MVC şablonunun yerini alır.
    [TR] İlgili: _Layout.cshtml (menü ve CTA bağlantıları tutarlı olmalı).

    MODIFICATION NOTES (TR)
    - Giriş yapan kullanıcıya /App veya pano yönlendirmesi eklenebilir.
    - İstatistik veya demo video alanı savunma için genişletilebilir.
    - OCR yalnızca PDF üzerinde seçilen bölge ile sınırlıdır; genel görüntü OCR aşağıda future work olarak belirtilmiştir.
    - Zorluk: Kolay.
*@
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<section class="app-hero text-white">
    <div class="container py-5 py-md-6">
        <div class="row align-items-center g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <p class="text-uppercase small fw-semibold opacity-75 letter-spacing mb-2">Graduation Project</p>
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold mb-3">Creative Document Translation and Visualisation System</h1>
                <p class="lead opacity-90 mb-4">
                    Upload academic and professional PDF documents, select a <strong>region</strong> on the page, extract text,
                    translate, summarize, and visualize it in one consistent workflow.
                </p>
                <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg px-4" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Login">Login</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg px-4" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register">Create Account</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5">
                <div class="app-hero-card rounded-4 p-4 text-dark shadow">
                    <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold mb-3">What does this system offer?</h2>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 small lh-lg">
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> PDF upload and page-level workspace</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> Rectangular region selection and coordinate storage</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> OCR over the <strong>selected PDF region only</strong></li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> Translation, summarization, and rewrite workflows</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> Text visualization and notebook/history</li>
                        <li><span class="text-accent me-2">&#10003;</span> Extensible service and provider layer</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="container py-5">
    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="h3 fw-bold mb-3">Project Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-muted lead fs-65 mb-0">
            The goal is to let users control the workflow by selecting <em>meaningful parts</em> inside a PDF document.
            The OCR engine is scoped to that selection to reduce noise and provide a better academic workflow.
            Translation, summarization, and rewriting run on the extracted text, and outputs can be visualized and stored in the notebook.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="h3 fw-bold mb-4 text-center">Features</h2>
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">PDF Upload</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Documents are imported into the system; page and metadata management can be expanded later.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Region Selection</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Users mark a rectangular region on the page and normalized coordinates are stored.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm border-start border-accent border-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">OCR (PDF Region)</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Text extraction is defined <strong>only</strong> for the selected PDF area; standalone image upload is outside this scope.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Translation and Summary</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Multilingual translation and summary generation run on OCR or edited text.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Rewrite</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Text can be rewritten according to style and target audience.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card app-card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Visualization and Notebook</h3>
                        <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Text analysis outputs can be supported with visuals or structured views, and history is retained.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="h3 fw-bold mb-3">Architecture Approach</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-3">
            The application layers are kept simple: web UI (ASP.NET Core MVC), business services, and thin adapters for external OCR/AI providers.
            This makes it possible to swap or run Tesseract, cloud APIs, or different translation engines side by side.
        </p>
        <div class="rounded-3 bg-light border p-4 small font-monospace text-secondary mb-0">
            Presentation -> Business logic -> Document/OCR interface -> Text processing (translation/summary/rewrite) -> Visualization & notebook
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <div class="alert alert-secondary border-0 rounded-3 shadow-sm d-flex flex-column flex-md-row align-items-md-center gap-3" role="note">
            <div class="fs-4 text-secondary" aria-hidden="true">&#9432;</div>
            <div>
                <strong>Out of scope (future work).</strong>
                General image-to-text extraction (random photos or standalone image OCR) is <em>not included in this version</em>.
                The system focuses on OCR over <strong>regions selected by the user inside a PDF</strong>.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="text-center py-4 rounded-4 app-cta-band">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-2">Get Started</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-3">Open the dashboard or upload a document to begin processing.</p>
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap justify-content-center gap-2">
            <a class="btn btn-accent btn-lg px-4" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Login">Login</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg px-4" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register">Register</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
